HEADWORD: Aliped
<hw>Al"i*ped</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>alipes</ets>; <ets>ala</ets> wing + <ets>pes</ets>,
<ets>pedis</ets>, foot: cf. F. <ets>alip⟦egrave⟧de</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Wing-footed, as the bat.</def> --
<def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>An animal whose toes are connected by a
membrane, serving for a wing, as the bat.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Aliphatic</ent>⟦br⟧
